## 🧠 DOMAIN RULES

> **The most critical section. Non-obvious rules that cause bugs when unknown. Derive nothing here from the code — only write what a new developer would NOT figure out in 30 minutes of reading.**

- —

_Examples of what belongs here: "User IDs are UUIDs in the API but integers in the DB — never expose the integer ID", "Prices are stored in cents, never floats", "The `active` flag on accounts is soft-delete — always filter by it", "Session tokens expire at midnight UTC regardless of creation time"._

