  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  FIRST-TIME SETUP — run this block once, never again.
  Triggered when: SESSION STATE is blank.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  STEP 1 — Detect stack
    Read: package.json, pyproject.toml, go.mod, Cargo.toml, Gemfile,
    composer.json, requirements.txt, Dockerfile, pubspec.yaml.
    Identify every technology in use. Then load its defaults from below.

  STEP 2 — Load stack defaults (structure + conventions + security)

    node-express   → src/controllers/ src/models/ src/routes/ src/middleware/ src/services/
                     camelCase files · MVC · async/await · JWT + helmet + CORS + rate-limit
    node-nest      → src/modules/*/controller.ts .service.ts .module.ts
                     PascalCase · decorators · DTOs · Guards + Pipes + JWT
    react          → src/components/ src/hooks/ src/pages/ src/context/ src/utils/
                     PascalCase components · co-located CSS modules · sanitize inputs
    next           → app/ or pages/ · app/api/ · components/ · lib/ · public/
                     file-based routing · RSC · server actions validation · middleware auth
    vue            → src/components/ src/views/ src/store/ src/router/ src/composables/
                     PascalCase SFCs · pinia · vue-router · route guards
    angular        → src/app/modules/ components/ services/ guards/
                     PascalCase · DI · NgModules · HTTP interceptors · XSS sanitization
    svelte         → src/lib/ src/routes/ src/components/ src/stores/
                     PascalCase · SvelteKit routing · input sanitization
    django         → apps/*/models.py views.py urls.py serializers.py
                     snake_case · DRF · CSRF + XSS + ORM (no raw SQL) + permission classes
    fastapi        → app/api/ app/models/ app/schemas/ app/core/ app/db/
                     snake_case · Pydantic schemas · OAuth2 + CORS + input validation
    flask          → app/routes/ app/models/ app/templates/ app/static/
                     snake_case · blueprints · app factory · Flask-Login + CSRFProtect
    go             → cmd/ internal/ pkg/ api/ migrations/
                     snake_case files · interface-based DI · JWT middleware · TLS · no raw SQL
    rust           → src/main.rs src/lib.rs src/bin/ src/modules/ tests/ benches/
                     snake_case · Result/Option · ownership safety · ring for crypto
    spring-boot    → src/main/java/../controller/ service/ repository/ model/ config/ security/
                     PascalCase · annotation-driven · Spring Security · OAuth2
    php-laravel    → app/Http/Controllers/ app/Models/ routes/ database/migrations/
                     PascalCase controllers · Eloquent · CSRF + XSS + auth gates
    ruby-rails     → app/controllers/ app/models/ app/views/ config/routes.rb db/migrate/
                     snake_case · RESTful · CSRF token · strong params · ActiveRecord
    flutter        → lib/screens/ lib/widgets/ lib/models/ lib/services/ lib/providers/
                     PascalCase widgets · BLoC/Provider · secure storage · cert pinning
    react-native   → src/screens/ src/navigation/ src/components/ src/hooks/
                     PascalCase · platform files (.ios.tsx .android.tsx) · secure storage
    svelte         → src/lib/ src/routes/ src/components/ src/stores/
    graphql        → src/graphql/schemas/ resolvers/ mutations/
                     SDL · dataloader · query depth limit · auth directives
    docker         → Dockerfile .dockerignore docker-compose.yml docker/
                     multi-stage builds · non-root user · no secrets in images
    database-pg    → migrations/ seeds/ db/ · parameterized queries only · row-level security
    database-mongo → src/models/ migrations/ seeds/ · sanitize input · no NoSQL injection
    database-prisma→ prisma/schema.prisma prisma/migrations/ src/repositories/
    database-redis → src/cache/ src/queues/ · TLS · auth token · key prefixing
    testing-jest   → tests/unit/ tests/__mocks__/ · mirror src/ · no secrets in tests
    testing-vitest → src/__tests__/ src/__mocks__/ · in-source testing · coverage thresholds
    testing-pytest → tests/ tests/conftest.py tests/fixtures/ · parametrize · isolated DB
    testing-playwright → e2e/ e2e/fixtures/ e2e/pages/ · page object model · no real tokens
    testing-cypress→ cypress/e2e/ cypress/fixtures/ cypress/support/ · no real auth tokens
    ci-github      → .github/workflows/ .github/actions/ · no secrets in logs · OIDC for cloud
    terraform      → terraform/ terraform/environments/ terraform/modules/
                     HCL · remote state · IAM least privilege · no secrets in state

  STEP 3 — Fill this file
    PROJECT IDENTITY   — infer from config files and package name
    STRUCTURE MAP      — scan, annotate every important file with its role
    SYMBOL INDEX       — key functions/classes + what they do (no line numbers)
    CONVENTIONS        — adapt to actual language; keep semantic naming rules
    DOMAIN RULES       — ask user: "What rule would cause a bug if I didn't know it?"
    SESSION STATE      — leave blank until end of first session

  STEP 4 — Ask only what cannot be inferred (one message, numbered list)
    - Project purpose, goals, and non-goals
    - Domain rules and business constraints
    - Current objective / where to start
    Never ask one question at a time.

  STEP 5 — Confirm and lock
    Show the filled file. Ask: "Does this match the project?"
    Once confirmed: stop scanning. Navigate via SYMBOL INDEX.
    Mark first setup as complete by writing SESSION STATE.

